This is Perl module CPAN::Command::Repo.

INSTALLATION

CPAN::Command::Repo installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan CPAN::Command::Repo

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

CPAN::Command::Repo documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc CPAN::Command::Repo

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

